{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token displayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let bold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size850, lineHeight: lineHeight1050, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing850)","        let bold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size1450, lineHeight: lineHeight1850, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.bold850, regular: FontRawTokens.bold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.bold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The case of this ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"text":" kit.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Since","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(compact:regular:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/compact","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/regular"],"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/fontToken(for:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/isEqual(_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" depending to size classes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kind of composite token with mu